Try using an external speaker, and/or sound chamber. The small 
internal chamber will tend to accentuate the higher noise frequencies-
-I think. I have the same system using the same chip, and use a 
really large external box with it. The echo box is nothing but an 
enclosure with a speaker on one side, and the mic on the other--use 
electret mic elements and 8 ohm speakers. The are jacks for external 
mic and speaker on #27. That&#39;s why I included that function. That 
chip&#39;s output is also very noisy, I don&#39;t know how to make it better. 

 Frank-S  




